reviews.text: OSU is a great college. Many smart kids come from all over the US and around the world to attend this school. They have great staffs and professors. We transport many of the wonderful students to/from Eugene Airport. The students always told us how much they love studying here. Thank you!!!
I had a chance to talk with some of your students. If you ask them to do critical thinking they look at you like deer in headlights. What the heck is this place teaching people?

The Pride Center and LGBTQ+ Multicultural Support Network at Oregon State University posted that they do not want a student VETERAN group to occupy a student lounge.

Vets “jeopardize” the wellbeing of students.  

Insanity.

A pride center at the Oregon State University posted via Facebook an open letter stating that a veterans student group is not welcome in the student lounge. They’ve since retracted said post, but never apologized. 

What they said, 

We aim to resist the pain that US militarism has caused our siblings in struggle and we denounce the glorification of the system that is responsible for this violence” the open letter continued. The letter also stated that the communities the organization serves are "vulnerable" when it comes to the "ideological and practical consequences" of letting the student veteran group into the space. 

Disgusting liberalism. Leftist fascism at its finest. Welcome to the tolerate leftist mindset.

In every county you will find an extension office of OSU, these wonderful folks will teach you the most basic absolutely necessary skill. Growth. Specific to your environment, science backed local information, so everyone can produce sustainably, thier hearts desire, as a Master Gardener.

This is our main store for shopping close to home! It can be pretty spendy at times with prices, but with Just4U coupons help a lot!! They have some great deals at times. If you want quality and a variety even with Safeway brands  Safeway is great for that. They have a deli, bakery and pharmacy. They also have a Starbucks inside. The one complaint I have lately with them is their meat department. The quality of their meat isn't as great as it use to be. We've found bone grit on the pork and bones in boneless skinless chicken. Otherwise I love their produce, breads, desserts and products!! Plus you'll always get GREAT customer service and asked if you need help out!! Or you can also do self checkout instead.

All and all it's not a bad place to shop... it's a little spendy... you definitely need to watch for deals... The cashiers are pretty nice..The pharmacy and their employees are Rock Stars... Trevor is one of the pharmacist who always goes above and beyond to take care of your needs... Thank you ever so much Trevor... yes, Amy your pretty awesome... Thank you kindly... :-) :-) :-)

This store is brightly lit and well maintained. We usually go to Costco for a lot of reasons but for small and unique grocery purchases we end up at Safeway. The checkers at this location are almost always pleasant and attentive, both things that aren't always guaranteed these days.
Its a grocery store chain. The quality is good. The price is a little high, but they offer a membership discount.

The old lady in the deli is absolutely the rudest person I’ve ever met in my life she constantly makes you feel like your bothering her that you want a sandwhich rolled her eyes and got huffy puffy that I asked for bacon and proceeded to say “I guess, but that’s gonna cost more” (like I didn’t already know that) then didn’t ask me if I wanted anything else threw my snadwhich on the counter and walked away. I will never be going back there again so disappointed

Probably the best authentic Mexican food in town. They have a few vegan/vegetarian options. Their rice is made with chicken stock, but they offer a meat-free option! And their beans are vegetarian. They don't offer free chips, so that might be a deterrent, but the food is so good and the reasonable prices make this a definite winner.

I have always gotten orders to go but we decided to sit down because they weren't packed like usual. I got Shrimp Fajitas and it was amazing. I got more toppings, vegetables, tortillas and shrimp than any other restaurant I have been before. The food was fast and delicious 🙂
Service here was top notch! Major kudos for that! The guy at the front was ON TOP OF IT!! Very impressed with him. Food was ok. Facilities mediocre.
Very delicious as usual. Red sauce is my favorite, but green is good too.
Great food. Always popular, so expect a wait, but the food is worth it.

The food is excellent. The atmosphere? Very casual. Essentially on campus, it is frequently standing room only. Take-out available. Cash orders over $10 get a bonus side. Credit or debit have a minimum total. Wide menu options.
This place is great! I always get their spicy ramen it is so good here. Plus the prices are decent. Staff is always friendly here.

A popular lunch spot, so it was busy at 12:30. The space is clean but small, with mismatched tables and paper menus tacked to the wall. The food is the star here, and it is delicious. The chicken yakisoba has perfectly grilled dark meat in it (my favorite), and the Beaver Roll is a lovely mix of tempura, avocado, cream cheese, salmon, and teriyaki. Lunch is between $7 and $14 a plate.
Great Japanese restaurant if you are looking to try new things. If you have never tried eel before this place would be a great first time by getting the Unagi Bowl.

The worst experience ever. The food I ordered was nothing but oil. It had no taste to it at all and I had to put lots of chillie sauce in order to eat it( I only ate half of it and threw the left overs anyway). Most importantly I feel that the guy in the counter must first learn to respect their customers without being a racist jerk. We all pay the same amount of money for a meal but why this stupid moron treats those with a white skin in one manner and those with a non-white skin in another? This is really shameful in a country which respects inclusivity of all people.

A great alternative sandwich store to the big chains (Subway, Jimmy John's and so on). Friendly staff, quick service, delicious sandwiches (one of the best breads I have ever had!) with fine prices, and downtown location. Definitely worth a try, and coming back whenever you're in the area.
Incredible service, comfortable and fun atmosphere, delicious food! I loved every part of my experience there.
I tried the Italian sandwich. Not a bad sandwich but not the best sandwich in town unfortunately. I will try something different next time and see if it is better.
Homemade breads, fresh toppings and friendly girls to help you.  Fast service as well
Decent food on a college budget. Has a bar attached with a good beer variety.
Delicious bread and fantastic bagels! I highly recommend stopping by for some fresh baked goodness. They also sell jam, coffee and crutons!
The best bread in Corvallis.

Larry is extremely passionate about the beautiful breads that he makes and it's apparent! Delicious naturally fermented sourdough, and a kind and knowledgeable owner. Each loaf costs about $7, they accept debit cards and they also have a small display of homemade desserts.
Real bread, real bakers and the real deal.  Simply the best and most local bread in Corvallis.
Wonderful fresh sour dough bread.  I recommend the dark rye!

Sushi is well made and well portioned. Service is attentive and there are buttons at each table for you to call a server without having to wave your arms about. Non-fish, meat meals are tasty as well and often come with a variety of sides on a small platter.

I ordered sushi. Simple rolls, just spicy tuna and salmon + avocado. They were poorly made; loose, way too much rice. Salmon and tuna didn’t taste bad but also did not taste very good. Dishes on other tables looked OK. Maybe it was just my sushi chef but, would not order sushi here again.

The food here was amazing. I enjoyed everything I tried and luckily I got there at happy hour without knowing it! Which started at 8:30 PM. The service here was very quick, and kind. I ordered my food and within 10 minutes I had my appetizer and entree. They made sure to check up on us as often. This is quickly becoming one of my favorite places to eat in the area.
Food was delicious. Like, bomb as f@ck. I think it’s ridiculous that a %15 tip is required, but the food was good enough for me to look past it. The wine was AMAZING. Thank You.
Best combination of both amazing entrees and sushi in town. Good Korean selection.

They always have great beer on tap, and the food is absolutely terrific. The food is eclectic and unique just like the atmosphere. I've been there for a show, and the cozy venue is exciting. And if you need to sit and take a break, the bar is a great escape.

Food and atmosphere are great. But the front bartender made it clear she was annoyed that she had to take my order back since they brought me the wrong food. Really no big deal, but if you get mad when you have to do your job just quit, don't make the customers feel bad for expecting service when it's offered
Great tacos, happy hour, and beer selection. A very lovely place (and kinda loud, no acoustic dampening), a good go to.
Jalepeno poppers are delicious, mojitos are awesome - staff very friendly

Bombs has some really good food. I recommend going there for lunch because the lunch specials are a lot cheaper. The specials let when I went the other day had about a dozen choices, ranging from about $6 to about $8. I had my favorite, the sizzling salad. Once you eat your greens, which is no problem because they're tasty, you uncover a delicious three-cheese enchilada! Yum.

I had forgotten about this restaurant. The menu offers a bit more than standard Mexican and we thought the food was quite good. Fantastic service and the place has good energy and a fun vibe. I especially enjoyed hearing the kitchen staff singing in back. That's always a good sign.

Prices are reasonable. Staff is friendly enough. Decent food. I have had better, but this is the best in Corvallis I have found so far. Depending on what you order, the amount of food is kinda small sometimes.
Great atmosphere & great service! I had the chicken chimichanga and enchilada lunch combo. It came with beans and rice. Delicious food. I highly recommend this restaurant.
I love the murals, they really took time to make this place beautiful. Lovely lime margaritas and yummy burritos.

Not impressed but not completely disappointed. You only get one bowl of chips and salsa and for anymore than that there is an additional charge. The food was alright, again... not impressed by any means and it wasn’t the worst I’ve ever had either. The service was decent too, no complaints there. The price really varied some things seemed like a good price while other things seemed extremely high. I don’t know if I would say I would recommend or not recommended going here because my experience was average.

Always a good mellow atmosphere for hanging out it dates. A very nice staff who are very welcoming and cheerful. They are also very prudent with their service. They have a great selection if products too. I would recommend this place for anyone asking for a great coffee place in Corvallis.

Great hidden Corvallis gem. They have a wide variety hot and cold beverages, including some fun ones like a Corvallis Fog (their unique twist on a London Fog). They have a several vegan "milk" choices. They also have great food. On the weekends they have an entire vegan brunch menu, as well as non-vegan brunch. And they always have a vegan food option during normal business hours. They even have vegan baked goods. The decor is also fun. The tables are retro, and they have a fun cassette/comic exchange library! This is just a great place to come and relax or meet friends for a coffee break. They also do concerts too!

The baristas pay close attention to the details and always pull an excellent double shot.  It is the type of place that makes you want to get a coffee drink and sit around for a while and read or write. I really appreciate some of the art on the walls and the retro style the tables and chairs.

Food is good, but they don't actually enforce the smoking laws outside, so if you want to eat outside on a nice day you should eat elsewhere. There were people sitting on the patio smoking for over an hour on a not busy day, so the staff definitely saw them and didn't feel like reminding them. Personally don't enjoy burritos with a side of second hand smoke

Interzone's coffee is great, and reasonably priced. Never tried their food or snacks; however, I strongly dislike that they have muffins and other pastry on the countertop, without any coverage, right at where everyone waits and pays and touches everything... no comment, but I wouldn't eat that.
The decoration is unique and fine, but most of the time it is hard to find a free spot to sit. They are good for a quick stop l, but would look elsewhere to sit down and catch up with a friend.

Excellent food, service, environment. Homemade, Vegan,  Delicious food.   Very peaceful,  delicious vegan food.   Definitely will go back again..!!  Super awesome lunch specials.  Excellent full  menu.  Self service dining.  
Highly recommend for your vegan dining in Corvallis.  They have cake!!!!  ☆☆☆☆☆

Been years since I was last here. The food here is just as good as it was 10+ years ago.  Very down to earth... Very much a free and hippie feel to the place. Food is tasty... healthy and very much comfort food.

One of the only vegetarian restaurants in town! And to simply put: Nearly Normals is must try spot, and not just for vegetarians!
Truly great meals, drinks and desert options. I love their ongoing specials; definitely tailored for OSU student's budget. Their house is amazing: awesome interior decor, feels like home environment. And the staff is on the top!

This is a lovely place. The staff is friendly and kind . The menu is very focused on vegetarian food from the 70s. It's great if that is what you are looking for. There's really nothing gluten free except for toast. No meat at all, so be prepared. Also, this is not a full service restaurant, so be prepared to order at the counter, get your own silver and water and bus your own table.   My least favorite, hubby's favorite.
Great food. The atmosphere is casual, "rustic". The business is celebrating 38 years. Could use some updating. Servers are friendly, helpful.

This place is very deceiving. It looks like a dive bar on the outside, but get inside and it looks very different. It has a rustic atmosphere where beautiful wood makes up the majority of the walls and tables. There's a bar top, tables, and booths to sit in. Take a staircase upstairs to another smaller level where you can play pool. There's only two pool tables but it's cozy there. They also serve food. I had the chef salad and it was surprisingly delicious and had a good portion size. Lots of various IPA's and ciders are sold here too. All in all, a very good place. I will go back for sure.

Best bar to find a respectable atmosphere and intelligent conversation; where chivalry is still present and not just another thing lost to the age of technology. ..... And the food is fantastic, too!
It's also cash only, so make sure you stop by an ATM on your way. At least with cash it's easier to stick to your own limit, because you can't just rack up a huge bill on your credit card. 😊

Home feel, professional staff. Great food and a nice tap.
A landmark for sure.
Classic "old man" bar. I love it. Fantastic burgers and atmosphere.
Great food & drinks. Also a great community supporter. Always donates to the Alsea Community Effort's annual Fundraiser and Raffle.
Rooms were clean but the hotel is very rundown. Everything smells smokey. Staff was friendly.
Every nice place
Well I don't know for shore but one time I seen wad olthon played a kidth katar

Poor customer service. I called to get a room . Lady seemed irritated that I was asking for a room an in a rude tone told me she needed my name an number so that her manager could go an see if there was any rooms. I told her no thx an called timberland  motel.very polite an gave me a room right away. Later I called big river back still same attitude.  Will sleep in truck before calling this place again . In the area alot for work so it's their loss.
Best staff.... Thank you!

Really no big deal, but if you get mad when you have to do your job just quit, don't make the customers feel bad for expecting service when it's offered

Once you eat your greens, which is no problem because they're tasty, you uncover a delicious three-cheese enchilada! Yum.

Closer to 4.5

This American-Mexican restaurant is a slightly-hidden gem with some standout menu offerings. Located in a strip mall sandwiched between a Dollar Store and an insurance company, one might be quick to dismiss this...but that would be a mistake. 

The restaurant itself is immaculately clean. Decor is bright and cheerful. Seating is a mix of booths and tables. I have had service ranging from disinterested to, literally, the best server experience in Corvallis.

Menu items are typical, but taste fresh and some nice attention to detail. May I recommend the Diabla burrito...a very spicy mixture of meat (I prefer shrimp), vegetables, and rice in a secret red sauce that is fire! Topped with sour cream and guacamole it is my favorite dish that never disappoints. 

The margaritas are strong and cold and the free chips come with salsa and beans.

This is a must!  Absolutely awesome service!  You're more like family than a customer!  The inside looks fantastic as well! 
Have you seen the bar in the back?! Phenomenal atmosphere if you're looking for a lighter ambience.
The food matches everything else!
Great prices for lunch. Pretty standard fair food but the place is clean and our waiter was attentive. Food was ready super quick. Definitely be back.

Pretty good for Mexican American food. I mean, it's not quite like dining in old Mexico, but that's a much longer drive. If you've never had it, you could order a plate with enchiladas. It comes with rice and beans. Or some grilled chicken. It also comes with rice and beans. But you get the point.
Pretty generic Mexican restaurant. Had enchiladas rancheras and it was good.
